In a saucepan, combine the milk and butter. Cook and stir over low heat until the butter is melted. Place the confectioners' sugar in a mixing bowl. Add milk mixture; beat until smooth. Add the coconut and orange extract; mix well. Roll into 1-in. balls; place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. In a saucepan, combine the chips, chocolate and shortening. Cook and stir over low heat until smooth. Dip balls into chocolate. Place on waxed paper until set.